==English==
===Etymology===
French ''[[#French|liard]]'', of unknown origin.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ljɑ:/, /ljɑ:d/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{historical}} A small French [[coin]], equivalent to a quarter of a [[sou]].
#:*'''1819''': “I waited — not to share the booty, for, so help me God and Saint Withold! as neither I nor any of mine will touch the value of a '''liard''', — I waited but to render my thanks to thee and to thy bold yeomen, for the life and honour ye have saved.” — Walter Scott, ''Ivanhoe''

